msgid ""
"Decode Canal MySQL binlog FlatMessage JSON carried by Kafka into "
"checkpointed Klein changelog rows."
msgstr "将 Kafka 承载的 Canal MySQL binlog FlatMessage JSON 解码为受检查点保护的 Klein 变更日志行。"

msgid "Canal JSON format"
msgstr "Canal JSON 格式"

msgid ""
"Klein consumes MySQL binlog changes that Canal Server publishes to Kafka "
"in FlatMessage JSON format. Canal JSON is a Kafka value format rather "
"than a physical connector. Install the Kafka dependency with:"
msgstr ""
"Klein 使用 Canal Server 以 FlatMessage JSON 格式发布到 Kafka 的 MySQL binlog "
"变更。Canal JSON 是一种 Kafka 值格式，而不是物理 Connector。请安装 Kafka 依赖："

msgid "Configure Canal with Kafka MQ mode and JSON messages:"
msgstr "将 Canal 配置为 Kafka MQ 模式并使用 JSON 消息："

msgid ""
"Canal's protobuf MQ payload (`canal.mq.flatMessage=false`) and the Canal "
"TCP client protocol are not supported by this format."
msgstr ""
"此格式不支持 Canal 的 protobuf MQ 载荷（`canal.mq.flatMessage=false`）和 Canal TCP "
"客户端协议。"

msgid "Read binlog changes"
msgstr "读取 binlog 变更"

msgid ""
"For convenience, `ray.klein.read_canal(...)` is a thin typed wrapper "
"around this call. It selects continuous Kafka and supplies `value_format`"
" and `format_options`; it does not introduce a Canal connector or a "
"second source implementation."
msgstr ""
"为便于使用，`ray.klein.read_canal(...)` 是此调用的轻量类型化封装。它会选择连续 Kafka，并提供 "
"`value_format` 和 `format_options`；它不会引入 Canal Connector 或第二套 Source 实现。"

msgid ""
"The format is continuous-only and uses the Kafka connector's "
"deterministic partition assignment, checkpointed offsets, partition "
"discovery, and durable checkpoint commit behavior."
msgstr "此格式仅支持连续模式，并使用 Kafka Connector 的确定性分区分配、检查点化 offset、分区发现和持久检查点提交行为。"

msgid "Change mapping"
msgstr "变更映射"

msgid "Canal type"
msgstr "Canal 类型"

msgid "Klein rows"
msgstr "Klein 行"

msgid "`INSERT`"
msgstr "`INSERT`"

msgid "One `RowKind.INSERT` for every `data` row."
msgstr "每个 `data` 行对应一个 `RowKind.INSERT`。"

msgid "`DELETE`"
msgstr "`DELETE`"

msgid "One `RowKind.DELETE` for every `data` row."
msgstr "每个 `data` 行对应一个 `RowKind.DELETE`。"

msgid "`UPDATE`"
msgstr "`UPDATE`"

msgid "An `UPDATE_BEFORE` and `UPDATE_AFTER` pair for every row."
msgstr "每个行对应一组 `UPDATE_BEFORE` 和 `UPDATE_AFTER`。"

msgid "DDL"
msgstr "DDL"

msgid ""
"Ignored, emitted as an INSERT metadata row, or rejected according to "
"`ddl_handling`."
msgstr "根据 `ddl_handling` 忽略、作为 INSERT 元数据行发出，或拒绝。"

msgid "Transaction/control event"
msgstr "事务/控制事件"

msgid "Ignored when it has no row data."
msgstr "没有行数据时忽略。"

msgid ""
"For UPDATE, Canal's `data` entry is the after image while its aligned "
"`old` entry contains the old values of changed columns. Klein overlays "
"`old` on `data` to reconstruct the complete before image. Missing or "
"misaligned `old` images fail fast because silently emitting an incorrect "
"retraction would corrupt downstream state."
msgstr ""
"对于 UPDATE，Canal 的 `data` 条目是后镜像，与其对齐的 `old` 条目包含已变更列的旧值。Klein 将 `old` 覆盖到"
" `data` 上，以重建完整的前镜像。缺失或未对齐的 `old` 镜像会快速失败，因为静默发出错误的撤回记录会破坏下游状态。"

msgid ""
"Canal FlatMessage values remain strings or `None`; Klein does not infer "
"Python values from `sqlType` or `mysqlType`. Cast fields explicitly in "
"application or SQL logic when numeric, temporal, or binary types are "
"required."
msgstr ""
"Canal FlatMessage 的值会保持为字符串或 `None`；Klein 不会根据 `sqlType` 或 `mysqlType` 推断"
" Python 值。需要数值、时间或二进制类型时，请在应用或 SQL 逻辑中显式转换字段。"

msgid "Metadata columns"
msgstr "元数据列"

msgid ""
"`format_options[\"include_metadata\"]=True` adds reserved columns without"
" replacing the row payload:"
msgstr "`format_options[\"include_metadata\"]=True` 会添加保留列，而不替换行载荷："

msgid ""
"`__canal_id`, `__canal_database`, `__canal_table`, and "
"`__canal_event_type`;"
msgstr "`__canal_id`、`__canal_database`、`__canal_table` 和 `__canal_event_type`；"

msgid ""
"`__canal_execute_time`, `__canal_build_time`, `__canal_gtid`, and "
"`__canal_pk_names` when present;"
msgstr ""
"存在时包括 `__canal_execute_time`、`__canal_build_time`、`__canal_gtid` 和 "
"`__canal_pk_names`；"

msgid ""
"`__canal_kafka_topic`, `__canal_kafka_partition`, and "
"`__canal_kafka_offset`."
msgstr "`__canal_kafka_topic`、`__canal_kafka_partition` 和 `__canal_kafka_offset`。"

msgid ""
"Set the option to `False` to emit only source-table columns. Reserved "
"metadata wins if a source table itself uses one of these names."
msgstr "将此选项设为 `False` 可仅发出源表列。如果源表本身使用了这些名称之一，保留元数据优先。"

msgid "DDL handling"
msgstr "DDL 处理"

msgid "`format_options[\"ddl_handling\"]` accepts:"
msgstr "`format_options[\"ddl_handling\"]` 接受："

msgid "`ignore` (default): advance the Kafka offset without emitting a row;"
msgstr "`ignore`（默认）：推进 Kafka offset，但不发出行；"

msgid ""
"`emit`: emit an INSERT metadata row containing `__canal_is_ddl=True` and "
"`__canal_sql`;"
msgstr "`emit`：发出一个包含 `__canal_is_ddl=True` 和 `__canal_sql` 的 INSERT 元数据行；"

msgid "`fail`: stop on a DDL event."
msgstr "`fail`：遇到 DDL 事件时停止。"

msgid "Recovery semantics"
msgstr "恢复语义"

msgid ""
"A single Canal Kafka record can contain several database rows, and every "
"UPDATE expands to two changelog rows. Klein checkpoints both the Kafka "
"offset and the next changelog-row index inside the current Kafka record. "
"A recovery therefore resumes at the exact before/after boundary instead "
"of dropping or replaying half of an UPDATE. Kafka group offsets are still"
" committed only after the corresponding Klein checkpoint is durable."
msgstr ""
"一条 Canal Kafka 记录可以包含多个数据库行，每个 UPDATE 会展开为两个变更日志行。Klein 会同时对 Kafka offset"
" 和当前 Kafka 记录内的下一个变更日志行索引创建检查点。因此，恢复会从准确的前/后镜像边界继续，而不会丢弃或重放 UPDATE "
"的一半。Kafka 消费组 offset 仍只会在对应的 Klein 检查点持久化后提交。"

msgid "Use Table DDL"
msgstr "使用 Table DDL"

msgid ""
"Use the Kafka connector with the `canal-json` format. Canal-specific SQL "
"options use the `canal-json.` namespace:"
msgstr ""
"请将 Kafka Connector 与 `canal-json` 格式配合使用。Canal 专用 SQL 选项使用 `canal-json.` "
"命名空间："

msgid ""
"`format='canal-json'` defaults the table source to continuous mode. Set "
"`trigger='continuous'` explicitly when a self-documenting DDL is "
"preferred. The format is source-only; Kafka sinks continue to use "
"`value_serializer`."
msgstr ""
"`format='canal-json'` 默认将表 Source 设为连续模式。如果希望 DDL 本身清楚表达意图，请显式设置 "
"`trigger='continuous'`。此格式仅用于 Source；Kafka Sink 继续使用 `value_serializer`。"

msgid "Ordering note"
msgstr "顺序说明"

msgid ""
"Klein preserves the order delivered by each Kafka partition. End-to-end "
"binlog ordering still depends on Canal's topic and partition routing. "
"Hashing by a primary key preserves order for that key but a primary-key "
"change can route the before and after operations differently; choose "
"Canal's routing configuration according to the downstream ordering "
"requirement."
msgstr ""
"Klein 会保留每个 Kafka 分区交付的顺序。端到端 binlog 顺序仍取决于 Canal 的 topic "
"和分区路由。按主键哈希可保留该键的顺序，但主键变更可能使前后操作被路由到不同位置；请根据下游顺序要求选择 Canal 的路由配置。"

msgid ""
"Create Klein for Ray inputs from Python collections, values, and existing"
" Ray Datasets."
msgstr "从 Python 集合、值和现有 Ray Dataset 创建 Klein for Ray 输入。"

msgid "Collections and existing Datasets"
msgstr "集合与现有 Dataset"

msgid ""
"Collection sources are useful for examples, tests, small control inputs, "
"and adapting an existing Ray Dataset. They are finite; they are not a "
"distributed queue or a replacement for a production data connector."
msgstr ""
"集合 Source 适用于示例、测试、小型控制输入以及适配现有 Ray Dataset。它们是有限的；既不是分布式队列，也不能替代生产数据 "
"Connector。"

