msgstr "`limit`"

msgid "`20`"
msgstr "`20`"

msgid ""
"Maximum rows shown by Ray Data in batch; maximum per sink subtask in "
"streaming. Use `-1` for no streaming limit."
msgstr "批处理模式下 Ray Data 显示的最大行数；流处理模式下每个 Sink Subtask 的最大行数。使用 `-1` 表示流处理不设限制。"

msgid "`num_cpus`"
msgstr "`num_cpus`"

msgid "`None`"
msgstr "`None`"

msgid "Sink task CPU requirement."
msgstr "Sink Task 的 CPU 要求。"

msgid "`concurrency`"
msgstr "`concurrency`"

msgid ""
"Number of streaming sink subtasks or Ray Data operation concurrency where"
" supported."
msgstr "流处理 Sink Subtask 的数量；在支持时也表示 Ray Data 操作并发度。"

msgid "`batch_size`"
msgstr "`batch_size`"

msgid "Maximum records delivered in one native operator batch."
msgstr "单个原生 Operator 批次交付的最大记录数。"

msgid "`batch_timeout`"
msgstr "`batch_timeout`"

msgid "3 seconds"
msgstr "3 秒"

msgid "Maximum wait for a native operator batch."
msgstr "等待原生 Operator 批次的最长时间。"

msgid "`name`"
msgstr "`name`"

msgid "`\"Show\"`"
msgstr "`\"Show\"`"

msgid "Operator name."
msgstr "Operator 名称。"

msgid ""
"In batch, `show` delegates to `Dataset.show`. In streaming, each output "
"line is compact JSON Lines and has this shape:"
msgstr "在批处理模式下，`show` 委托给 `Dataset.show`。在流处理模式下，每个输出行都是紧凑的 JSON Lines，格式如下："

msgid ""
"For a `ChangelogRow`, the line also includes `row_kind`. Operational logs"
" use standard error so tools can safely parse or pipe standard output. "
"Sequence and limit counters are local to each streaming subtask."
msgstr ""
"对于 `ChangelogRow`，行中还会包含 "
"`row_kind`。运维日志使用标准错误，因此工具可以安全地解析标准输出或将其接入管道。序列计数器和限制计数器均为各流处理 Subtask "
"所独有。"

msgid ""
"Checkpoint recovery can print a record again. Do not treat console output"
" as an exactly-once audit log, and avoid it for high-volume production "
"data."
msgstr "检查点恢复可能再次打印记录。不要将 console 输出视为 exactly-once 审计日志，也不要将其用于高吞吐生产数据。"

msgid "The sink-only Table connector identifier is `print`:"
msgstr "仅支持 Sink 的 Table Connector 标识符为 `print`："

msgid ""
"`limit` defaults to `20` and is the only connector option. The print sink"
" accepts all Klein row kinds and includes `row_kind` in native streaming "
"output. See [SQL and Table DDL](../sql.md) for inserting a query into the"
" table."
msgstr ""
"`limit` 默认为 `20`，也是唯一的 Connector 选项。print Sink 接受所有 Klein "
"行类型，并在原生流处理输出中包含 `row_kind`。有关将查询插入表中的方法，请参阅 [SQL 与 Table "
"DDL](../sql.md)。"

msgid ""
"Implement custom Klein for Ray SourceFunction, SinkFunction, two-phase-"
"commit sink, and TableFactory connectors."
msgstr ""
"实现自定义 Klein for Ray SourceFunction、SinkFunction、两阶段提交 Sink 和 TableFactory"
" Connector。"

msgid "Custom connectors"
msgstr "自定义 Connector"

msgid ""
"Use a custom connector when an external system has no public Ray Data "
"adapter and no built-in Klein integration. Native `SourceFunction` and "
"`SinkFunction` connectors execute only on Klein's streaming runtime "
"unless you also provide an internal Ray Data lowering."
msgstr ""
"当外部系统没有公开的 Ray Data 适配器，也没有内置 Klein 集成时，请使用自定义 Connector。除非还提供内部 Ray Data"
" lowering，否则原生 `SourceFunction` 和 `SinkFunction` Connector 只能在 Klein "
"流处理运行时中执行。"

msgid "Implement a source"
msgstr "实现 Source"

msgid ""
"A source class implements `run`, `cancel`, `snapshot_state`, and "
"`restore_state`. It may implement `open`, `close`, and "
"`notify_checkpoint_complete` for lifecycle and external offset commits."
msgstr ""
"Source 类需实现 `run`、`cancel`、`snapshot_state` 和 `restore_state`。它还可以实现 "
"`open`、`close` 和 `notify_checkpoint_complete`，以处理生命周期和外部 offset 提交。"

msgid ""
"Pass the class, not a preconstructed instance, so every Ray task owns its"
" resources. `fn_constructor_args` and `fn_constructor_kwargs` are "
"serialized as top-level actor-construction arguments. `num_cpus`, "
"`num_gpus`, and `concurrency` control source resources; `bounded` records"
" finiteness but does not make a native source batch-lowerable. A bounded "
"native source without a lowering must force streaming as shown above. "
"Declare `changelog_mode` when the source can emit non-insert `RowKind` "
"values."
msgstr ""
"请传入类而不是预先构造的实例，使每个 Ray Task 都拥有自己的资源。`fn_constructor_args` 和 "
"`fn_constructor_kwargs` 会作为顶层 Actor 构造参数序列化。`num_cpus`、`num_gpus` 和 "
"`concurrency` 控制 Source 资源；`bounded` 记录其是否有限，但不会使原生 Source 可 lowering "
"为批处理。没有 lowering 的有界原生 Source 必须像上例一样强制使用流处理。当 Source 可以发出非 insert "
"`RowKind` 值时，请声明 `changelog_mode`。"

msgid ""
"`SourceContext.collect()` accepts mapping records and preserves source "
"order. Advance the externally meaningful position before calling "
"`collect`, as in the example, so a barrier caused by that call snapshots "
"the matching next position. The other context methods are:"
msgstr ""
"`SourceContext.collect()` 接受映射记录并保留 Source 顺序。请像示例中那样，在调用 `collect` "
"前推进对外有意义的位置，使该调用触发的 Barrier 对匹配的下一个位置创建快照。其他 Context 方法如下："

msgid "Method"
msgstr "方法"

msgid "When to use it"
msgstr "使用时机"

msgid "`on_idle()`"
msgstr "`on_idle()`"

msgid ""
"A blocking poll returned no data; lets time checkpoints and watermark "
"idleness advance."
msgstr "阻塞轮询未返回数据时调用；使定时检查点和 Watermark 空闲状态可以推进。"

msgid "`emit_watermark(timestamp)`"
msgstr "`emit_watermark(timestamp)`"

msgid "All preceding records are at or before explicit event-time progress."
msgstr "之前的所有记录均不晚于显式事件时间进度。"

msgid "`mark_idle()`"
msgstr "`mark_idle()`"

msgid "Exclude this input from downstream minimum-watermark calculation."
msgstr "从下游最小 Watermark 计算中排除此输入。"

msgid "`mark_active(resume_watermark=None)`"
msgstr "`mark_active(resume_watermark=None)`"

msgid "Reactivate before emitting after an idle period."
msgstr "空闲一段时间后，在发出数据前重新激活。"

msgid "`ray.klein.source` registration options are:"
msgstr "`ray.klein.source` 注册选项如下："

msgid "`fn`"
msgstr "`fn`"

msgid "Required"
msgstr "必填"

msgid "`SourceFunction` class; instances are rejected."
msgstr "`SourceFunction` 类；不接受实例。"

msgid "`fn_constructor_args`, `fn_constructor_kwargs`"
msgstr "`fn_constructor_args`、`fn_constructor_kwargs`"

msgid "Arguments used to construct one source per subtask."
msgstr "用于为每个 Subtask 构造一个 Source 的参数。"

msgid "`lowering`"
msgstr "`lowering`"

msgid "Advanced declarative Ray Data source lowering for batch support."
msgstr "用于支持批处理的高级声明式 Ray Data Source lowering。"

msgid "`num_cpus`, `num_gpus`"
msgstr "`num_cpus`、`num_gpus`"

msgid "Effective defaults are 1 CPU and 0 GPUs."
msgstr "实际默认值为 1 个 CPU 和 0 个 GPU。"

msgid "Effective parallelism 1; an integer or `(min, max)` range is accepted."
msgstr "实际并行度默认为 1；接受整数或 `(min, max)` 范围。"

msgid "Logical operator name."
msgstr "逻辑 Operator 名称。"

msgid "`bounded`"
msgstr "`bounded`"

msgid "`False`"
msgstr "`False`"

msgid "Whether the source is finite; independent of batch support."
msgstr "Source 是否有限；与批处理支持无关。"

msgid "`changelog_mode`"
msgstr "`changelog_mode`"

msgid "Optional non-empty set of emitted `RowKind` values."
msgstr "可选的非空已发出 `RowKind` 值集合。"

msgid ""
"Source snapshot state must be pickleable. `notify_checkpoint_complete` is"
" at-least-once across coordinator recovery, so use the checkpoint ID as "
"an idempotency key when committing offsets externally. `cancel` should "
"only signal the run loop; release clients, files, and threads in `close`."
msgstr ""
"Source 快照状态必须可被 pickle。Coordinator 恢复时，`notify_checkpoint_complete` 具有 "
"at-least-once 语义，因此在外部提交 offset 时，请使用检查点 ID 作为幂等键。`cancel` 应仅向运行循环发出信号；请在"
" `close` 中释放客户端、文件和线程。"

msgid "Implement a sink"
msgstr "实现 Sink"

msgid "Subclass `SinkFunction` for an ordinary streaming sink:"
msgstr "为普通流处理 Sink 创建 `SinkFunction` 子类："

msgid ""
"`DataStream.write` accepts the same constructor, resource, concurrency, "
"and name options. It additionally accepts operator `batch_size` (default "
"`None`) and `batch_timeout` (default 3 seconds), plus an advanced "
"`lowering` for Ray Data batch support. Leave the internal `node_type` "
"override unset in connector code."
msgstr ""
"`DataStream.write` 接受相同的构造、资源、并发度和名称选项。它还接受 Operator `batch_size`（默认 "
"`None`）和 `batch_timeout`（默认 3 秒），以及用于支持 Ray Data 批处理的高级 `lowering`。在 "
"Connector 代码中，请勿设置内部 `node_type` 覆盖项。"

msgid ""
"`write(value)` receives one mapping. `flush()` is called where buffered "
"output must be drained, including checkpoint alignment. Connector clients"
" should be constructed in `open`, not serialized from the driver. A "
"normal `SinkFunction` does not gain exactly-once semantics merely by "
"flushing at a barrier; document the external system's replay and "
"idempotency behavior."
msgstr ""
"`write(value)` 接收一个映射。在必须排空缓冲输出时（包括检查点对齐）会调用 `flush()`。Connector 客户端应在 "
"`open` 中构造，而不是从 Driver 序列化。普通 `SinkFunction` 不会仅因在 Barrier 处刷新就获得 "
"exactly-once 语义；请说明外部系统的重放和幂等行为。"

msgid "Implement a two-phase-commit sink"
msgstr "实现两阶段提交 Sink"

msgid ""
"Use `TwoPhaseCommitSinkFunction` only when prepared output can remain "
"private until a global checkpoint is durable. In addition to `write`, "
"implement:"
msgstr ""
"仅当已准备的输出能够在全局检查点持久化前保持私有时，才使用 `TwoPhaseCommitSinkFunction`。除 `write` "
"外，还需实现："

msgid ""
"`prepare_commit(checkpoint_id)`, which closes the current transaction, "
"starts a fresh one, and returns a pickleable `SinkCommittable` or `None` "
"for no data;"
msgstr ""
"`prepare_commit(checkpoint_id)`：关闭当前事务、启动新事务，并返回可被 pickle 的 "
"`SinkCommittable`；没有数据时返回 `None`；"

msgid ""
"`abort_current_transaction()`, which discards writer-local unprepared "
"data."
msgstr "`abort_current_transaction()`：丢弃 Writer 本地尚未准备的数据。"

msgid ""
"A `SinkCommittable` supplies a stable string `transaction_id` and "
"idempotent `commit()` and `abort()` methods. It must store only enough "
"serializable information to reconnect and publish or discard the prepared"
" transaction; do not capture clients, locks, threads, or open handles. "
"The coordinator persists the committable before calling `commit` and may "
"retry either terminal method after recovery. The [filesystem "
"connector](filesystem.md) is the reference implementation."
msgstr ""
"`SinkCommittable` 提供稳定的字符串 `transaction_id`，以及幂等的 `commit()` 和 `abort()` "
"方法。它只应存储足够的可序列化信息，用于重新连接并发布或丢弃已准备事务；不要捕获客户端、锁、线程或打开的句柄。Coordinator 会在调用 "
"`commit` 前持久化 Committable，并可能在恢复后重试任一终止方法。[Filesystem "
"Connector](filesystem.md) 是参考实现。"

msgid "Add a Table DDL connector"
msgstr "添加 Table DDL Connector"

msgid ""
"Subclass `TableFactory`, set a non-empty `identifier`, and implement only"
" the directions the connector supports:"
msgstr "创建 `TableFactory` 子类，设置非空 `identifier`，并仅实现 Connector 支持的方向："

msgid "Responsibility"
msgstr "职责"

msgid "`validate(table)`"
msgstr "`validate(table)`"

msgid "Reject missing, malformed, or unknown connector options eagerly."
msgstr "尽早拒绝缺失、格式错误或未知的 Connector 选项。"

msgid "`create_source(context, table)`"
msgstr "`create_source(context, table)`"

msgid "Convert catalog metadata to a `DataStream`."
msgstr "将 Catalog 元数据转换为 `DataStream`。"

msgid "`create_sink(stream, table)`"
msgstr "`create_sink(stream, table)`"

msgid "Bind a stream to connector output."
msgstr "将 Stream 绑定到 Connector 输出。"

msgid "`supported_sink_row_kinds(table)`"
msgstr "`supported_sink_row_kinds(table)`"

msgid "Declare accepted changelog kinds; default is insert-only."
msgstr "声明接受的变更日志类型；默认仅接受 insert。"

msgid "Register an instance in one SQL session:"
msgstr "在一个 SQL Session 中注册实例："

msgid ""
"For an installable connector package, publish a Python entry point in the"
" `ray.klein.table_factories` group. The entry point may resolve to a "
"factory instance or class. Klein discovers these alongside the built-in "
"`filesystem`, `kafka`, and `print` factories. Duplicate identifiers fail "
"unless a session-local registration explicitly uses `replace=True`."
msgstr ""
"对于可安装的 Connector 包，请在 `ray.klein.table_factories` 组中发布 Python Entry "
"Point。该 Entry Point 可以解析为 Factory 实例或类。Klein 会将它们与内置 `filesystem`、`kafka`"
" 和 `print` Factory 一起发现。重复标识符会导致失败，除非 Session 本地注册显式使用 `replace=True`。"

msgid ""
"See [SQL and Table DDL](../sql.md) for catalog behavior and "
"[Testing](../testing.md) for connector test expectations."
msgstr ""
"有关 Catalog 行为，请参阅 [SQL 与 Table DDL](../sql.md)；有关 Connector "
"测试要求，请参阅[测试](../testing.md)。"

msgid ""
"Read files with Ray Data and write checkpoint-transactional JSON, CSV, "
"Parquet, and text files with Klein for Ray."
msgstr "使用 Ray Data 读取文件，并通过 Klein for Ray 写入具备检查点事务语义的 JSON、CSV、Parquet 和文本文件。"

msgid "Filesystem"
msgstr "Filesystem"

msgid ""
"Filesystem input uses public Ray Data readers and is bounded. Klein's "
"stable output API writes JSON, CSV, and Parquet in either execution mode "
"and text in streaming mode. Native streaming output participates in Klein"
" checkpoints so uncommitted part files are not exposed as completed "
"output."
msgstr ""
"Filesystem 输入使用公开的 Ray Data Reader，并且是有界的。Klein 的稳定输出 API 可在两种执行模式下写入 "
"JSON、CSV 和 Parquet，并可在流处理模式下写入文本。原生流处理输出参与 Klein 检查点，因此未提交的 part "
"文件不会作为已完成输出暴露。"

msgid "Read files"
msgstr "读取文件"

msgid ""
"Use any public Ray Data file reader exposed by the installed compatible "
"Ray version:"
msgstr "可使用已安装兼容 Ray 版本公开的任意 Ray Data 文件 Reader："

msgid ""
"Common readers include `read_csv`, `read_json`, `read_parquet`, and "
"`read_text`. Their options, schemas, file discovery, and retry semantics "
"are owned by Ray Data; see [Ray Data](ray-data.md). Filesystem input has "
"no native continuous directory watcher."
msgstr ""
"常用 Reader 包括 `read_csv`、`read_json`、`read_parquet` 和 "
"`read_text`。它们的选项、schema、文件发现和重试语义由 Ray Data 管理；请参阅 [Ray Data](ray-"
"data.md)。Filesystem 输入没有原生连续目录监视器。"

msgid "Write files"
msgstr "写入文件"

msgid ""
"Call `write_json`, `write_csv`, `write_parquet`, `write_text`, or the "
"common `write_files(path, data_format, ...)` method."
msgstr ""
"调用 `write_json`、`write_csv`、`write_parquet`、`write_text`，或通用的 "
"`write_files(path, data_format, ...)` 方法。"

msgid "`path`"
msgstr "`path`"

msgid "Output directory on a local, shared, or object filesystem."
msgstr "本地、共享或对象文件系统上的输出目录。"

msgid "`data_format`"
msgstr "`data_format`"

msgid "Required to `write_files`"
msgstr "`write_files` 必填"

msgid "`json`, `csv`, `parquet`, or `text`."
msgstr "`json`、`csv`、`parquet` 或 `text`。"

msgid "`columns`"
msgstr "`columns`"

msgid "Explicit column order; text requires exactly one column."
msgstr "显式列顺序；文本格式要求恰好一列。"

msgid "`storage_options`"
msgstr "`storage_options`"

msgid "PyArrow filesystem construction options for native streaming."
msgstr "用于原生流处理的 PyArrow 文件系统构造选项。"

msgid "`filename_prefix`"
msgstr "`filename_prefix`"

msgid "`\"part\"`"
msgstr "`\"part\"`"

msgid "Prefix for final part filenames."
msgstr "最终 part 文件名的前缀。"

msgid "`max_rows_per_file`"
msgstr "`max_rows_per_file`"

msgid "Positive row-count rolling threshold."
msgstr "正数行数滚动阈值。"

msgid "`max_bytes_per_file`"
msgstr "`max_bytes_per_file`"

msgid "Positive encoded-byte rolling threshold."
msgstr "正数编码字节数滚动阈值。"

msgid "`rollover_interval`"
msgstr "`rollover_interval`"

msgid "Maximum duration a part remains open."
msgstr "part 保持打开的最长时间。"

msgid "`inactivity_interval`"
msgstr "`inactivity_interval`"

msgid "Close an inactive part at the next write or checkpoint."
msgstr "在下次写入或检查点时关闭不活跃的 part。"

msgid "`ray_remote_args`"
msgstr "`ray_remote_args`"

msgid ""
"Ray Data batch options; `num_cpus` and `num_gpus` also size native sink "
"tasks."
msgstr "Ray Data 批处理选项；`num_cpus` 和 `num_gpus` 也用于确定原生 Sink Task 的资源大小。"

msgid "Batch writer concurrency or native sink parallelism."
msgstr "批处理 Writer 并发度或原生 Sink 并行度。"

msgid "`ray_data_options`"
msgstr "`ray_data_options`"

msgid "Extra options forwarded only to the bounded Ray Data writer."
msgstr "仅转发给有界 Ray Data Writer 的额外选项。"

msgid ""
"Streaming records must be mappings. JSON is newline-delimited; every CSV "
"part contains its own header. Text output encodes the single selected "
"column as UTF-8. JSON, CSV, and Parquet lower to their Ray Data writers "
"in batch; text does not have a Klein batch lowering and therefore "
"requires streaming mode. In batch, only `path`, `data_format`, "
"`ray_data_options`, `ray_remote_args`, and `concurrency` affect the Ray "
"Data write. Column order, storage options, filename prefix, and rolling "
"policies are native-streaming settings and are not forwarded to Ray Data."
msgstr ""
"流处理记录必须是映射。JSON 使用换行分隔；每个 CSV part 都包含自己的表头。文本输出将选中的唯一列编码为 UTF-8。JSON、CSV"
" 和 Parquet 在批处理模式下会 lowering 到对应的 Ray Data Writer；文本没有 Klein 批处理 "
"lowering，因此需要流处理模式。在批处理模式下，只有 "
"`path`、`data_format`、`ray_data_options`、`ray_remote_args` 和 `concurrency`"
" 会影响 Ray Data 写入。列顺序、存储选项、文件名前缀和滚动策略是原生流处理设置，不会转发给 Ray Data。"

msgid "Understand the streaming commit lifecycle"
msgstr "理解流处理提交生命周期"

msgid "Each streaming sink subtask owns a unique attempt directory:"
msgstr "每个流处理 Sink Subtask 都拥有唯一的 attempt 目录："

msgid ""
"At an aligned checkpoint barrier, the writer closes its in-progress part "
"and returns a serializable committable. The coordinator then:"
msgstr ""
"在对齐的检查点 Barrier 处，Writer 会关闭正在写入的 part，并返回可序列化的 Committable。随后 "
"Coordinator 会："

msgid ""
"persists source state, operator state, and sink committables in "
"checkpoint metadata;"
msgstr "在检查点元数据中持久化 Source 状态、Operator 状态和 Sink Committable；"

msgid "publishes pending parts to final paths with idempotent commits;"
msgstr "通过幂等提交将待处理 part 发布到最终路径；"

msgid "notifies checkpoint-aware sources that the checkpoint is durable."
msgstr "通知感知检查点的 Source 该检查点已持久化。"

msgid ""
"Recovery reloads persisted committables and retries publication. An "
"already published target completes successfully instead of producing "
"another part. Klein aborts prepared files from an abandoned checkpoint "
"when possible."
msgstr ""
"恢复会重新加载已持久化的 Committable 并重试发布。已发布的目标会成功完成，而不会生成另一个 part。Klein "
"会尽可能中止已放弃检查点中的已准备文件。"

msgid ""
"This provides **exactly-once file visibility relative to Klein "
"checkpoints**. Use durable shared storage for both "
"`execution.checkpointing.dir` and output. Force termination or an "
"unreachable object store can leave hidden staging objects, but readers "
"that ignore `.klein-staging` do not treat them as output."
msgstr ""
"这提供了**相对于 Klein 检查点的 exactly-once 文件可见性**。`execution.checkpointing.dir` "
"和输出都应使用持久共享存储。强制终止或对象存储不可达可能留下隐藏的暂存对象，但忽略 `.klein-staging` 的 Reader "
"不会将其视为输出。"

msgid "Configure rolling"
msgstr "配置滚动策略"

msgid ""
"Every checkpoint rolls the active part. You may roll earlier by row "
"count, encoded bytes, elapsed time, or inactivity:"
msgstr "每个检查点都会滚动当前活跃的 part。也可以根据行数、编码字节数、已用时间或不活跃状态提前滚动："

msgid ""
"Rolling prepares a private file; publication still waits for a successful"
" checkpoint. Time policies are evaluated on writes and at the next "
"checkpoint, not by a separate per-part timer."
msgstr "滚动会准备一个私有文件；发布仍需等待检查点成功。时间策略在写入时和下一个检查点处评估，而不是由每个 part 的独立计时器评估。"

msgid "The connector identifier is `filesystem`:"
msgstr "Connector 标识符为 `filesystem`："

msgid ""
"`path` and `format` are required. Source options use a `source.` prefix "
"and are forwarded to the matching Ray Data reader, for example "
"`source.override_num_blocks`. Sink options are:"
msgstr ""
"`path` 和 `format` 为必填项。Source 选项使用 `source.` 前缀，并转发给匹配的 Ray Data "
"Reader，例如 `source.override_num_blocks`。Sink 选项如下："

msgid "Table option"
msgstr "Table 选项"

msgid "`sink.filename-prefix`"
msgstr "`sink.filename-prefix`"

msgid "`part`"
msgstr "`part`"

msgid "Final filename prefix."
msgstr "最终文件名前缀。"

msgid "`sink.max-rows-per-file`"
msgstr "`sink.max-rows-per-file`"

msgid "None"
msgstr "None"

msgid "Positive row-count threshold."
msgstr "正数行数阈值。"

msgid "`sink.parallelism`"
msgstr "`sink.parallelism`"

msgid "Positive native sink parallelism."
msgstr "正数原生 Sink 并行度。"

msgid "`sink.rolling-policy.file-size`"
msgstr "`sink.rolling-policy.file-size`"

msgid "Bytes or a size such as `128 MB` or `128 MiB`."
msgstr "字节数，或 `128 MB`、`128 MiB` 之类的大小。"

msgid "`sink.rolling-policy.rollover-interval`"
msgstr "`sink.rolling-policy.rollover-interval`"

msgid "Positive duration such as `15 min`."
msgstr "正数时长，例如 `15 min`。"

msgid "`sink.rolling-policy.inactivity-interval`"
msgstr "`sink.rolling-policy.inactivity-interval`"

msgid "Positive inactivity duration."
msgstr "正数不活跃时长。"

msgid "`sink.storage-options`"
msgstr "`sink.storage-options`"

msgid "JSON object for the native PyArrow filesystem."
msgstr "用于原生 PyArrow 文件系统的 JSON 对象。"

msgid "`sink.ray-data-options`"
msgstr "`sink.ray-data-options`"

msgid "JSON object forwarded only to bounded output."
msgstr "仅转发给有界输出的 JSON 对象。"

msgid ""
"Supported DDL formats are `csv`, `json`, `parquet`, and `text`. A text "
"sink table must have exactly one column. See [SQL and Table "
"DDL](../sql.md) for full statement behavior."
msgstr ""
"支持的 DDL 格式为 `csv`、`json`、`parquet` 和 `text`。文本 Sink "
"表必须恰好包含一列。有关完整语句行为，请参阅 [SQL 与 Table DDL](../sql.md)。"

msgid "Credentials and operations"
msgstr "凭据与运维"

msgid ""
"Prefer workload identity, instance roles, or the filesystem client's "
"standard credential chain over secrets in `storage_options`. Checkpoint "
"metadata stores serialized transactions, so do not put non-serializable "
"filesystem clients in connector options. Monitor checkpoint duration and "
"failures as described in [Observability](../observability.md)."
msgstr ""
"应优先使用工作负载身份、实例角色或文件系统客户端的标准凭据链，而不是在 `storage_options` "
"中放置密钥。检查点元数据会存储序列化事务，因此不要在 Connector "
"选项中放置不可序列化的文件系统客户端。请按照[可观测性](../observability.md)中的说明监控检查点耗时和失败。"

msgid ""
"Write Ray Data batches or checkpoint-transactional streaming appends to "
"Apache Iceberg with Klein for Ray."
msgstr "使用 Klein for Ray 向 Apache Iceberg 写入 Ray Data 批次或具备检查点事务语义的流式追加。"

msgid "Apache Iceberg"
msgstr "Apache Iceberg"

msgid "Install the Iceberg extra on the driver and every streaming worker:"
msgstr "在 Driver 和每个流处理 Worker 上安装 Iceberg extra："

msgid ""
"`DataStream.write_iceberg()` has the same arguments as the compatible Ray"
" Data `Dataset.write_iceberg()` API. The table and namespace must already"
" exist. Catalog configuration follows PyIceberg:"
msgstr ""
"`DataStream.write_iceberg()` 的参数与兼容 Ray Data `Dataset.write_iceberg()` "
"API 相同。表和命名空间必须已存在。Catalog 配置遵循 PyIceberg："

msgid "Execution modes"
msgstr "执行模式"

msgid "Mode"
msgstr "模式"

msgid "Behavior"
msgstr "行为"

msgid ""
"Delegates to Ray Data and supports its append, overwrite, upsert, schema "
"evolution, and concurrency behavior."
msgstr "委托给 Ray Data，并支持其 append、overwrite、upsert、schema 演进和并发行为。"

msgid ""
"Supports `SaveMode.APPEND`; non-empty sink subtasks prepare Arrow "
"batches, which the coordinator combines per logical sink and domain epoch"
" before publishing one durable Iceberg snapshot."
msgstr ""
"支持 `SaveMode.APPEND`；非空 sink 子任务会准备 Arrow 批次，协调器按逻辑 sink 和检查点域 epoch "
"合并这些批次，然后发布一个持久的 Iceberg snapshot。"

msgid ""
"Streaming overwrite and upsert are rejected. An overwrite committed by "
"one parallel sink subtask would erase output from other subtasks, while a"
" correct streaming upsert needs a global key/materialization contract. "
"Use a bounded Ray Data job for those modes."
msgstr ""
"流处理 overwrite 和 upsert 会被拒绝。一个并行 Sink Subtask 提交的 overwrite 会擦除其他 Subtask"
" 的输出，而正确的流处理 upsert 需要全局键/物化契约。请为这些模式使用有界 Ray Data 作业。"

msgid "Checkpoint and schema behavior"
msgstr "检查点与 schema 行为"

msgid ""
"Prepared Arrow batches are compressed into Klein checkpoint metadata. "
"Keep the checkpoint interval and source rate sized so one interval fits "
"comfortably in checkpoint storage and coordinator memory. Increasing sink"
" concurrency reduces the batch held by each subtask; writers "
"participating in the same checkpoint domain epoch are committed in one "
"Iceberg append. Physically disconnected domains still checkpoint and "
"commit independently."
msgstr ""
"已准备的 Arrow 批次会压缩到 Klein "
"检查点元数据中。请合理设置检查点间隔和源速率，使一个间隔内的数据能轻松容纳在检查点存储和协调器内存中。提高 sink "
"并发度会减少每个子任务持有的批次大小；参与同一检查点域 epoch 的 writer 会在一次 Iceberg append "
"中提交。物理上断开的域仍会独立执行检查点和提交。"

msgid ""
"The commit adds a reserved `ray-klein.transaction-id` snapshot property. "
"On a coordinator retry, Klein reloads the table and treats a snapshot "
"with the same transaction ID as already committed. Do not set that "
"property yourself, and do not expire a just-committed snapshot while its "
"Klein checkpoint is still being finalized."
msgstr ""
"提交会添加保留的 `ray-klein.transaction-id` snapshot 属性。Coordinator 重试时，Klein "
"会重新加载表，并将具有相同事务 ID 的 snapshot 视为已提交。请勿自行设置该属性，也不要在对应 Klein "
"检查点仍处于最终确认阶段时过期刚提交的 snapshot。"

msgid ""
"New top-level columns are added before the data snapshot while existing "
"Iceberg field IDs and required identifier columns are preserved. Rows "
"handled by one live sink task must keep the same set of columns. Nested "
"schema changes and incompatible type changes should be applied to the "
"table separately before the stream emits the new shape."
msgstr ""
"新的顶层列会在数据 snapshot 前添加，同时保留现有 Iceberg 字段 ID 和必需的标识列。一个运行中 Sink Task "
"处理的行必须保持相同的列集合。嵌套 schema 变更和不兼容的类型变更应先单独应用到表，再让 Stream 发出新结构。"

msgid ""
"Catalog credentials are serialized as part of the job and prepared "
"checkpoint transaction. Prefer workload identity or the catalog/FileIO "
"credential chain over embedding long-lived secrets in `catalog_kwargs`."
msgstr ""
"Catalog 凭据会作为作业和已准备检查点事务的一部分序列化。应优先使用工作负载身份或 Catalog/FileIO 凭据链，而不是在 "
"`catalog_kwargs` 中嵌入长期密钥。"

msgid ""
"Klein for Ray connector catalog for Ray Data, collections, Kafka, "
"RocketMQ, filesystems, Redis, console, custom connectors, and Ray Serve."
msgstr ""
"Klein for Ray Connector 目录，涵盖 Ray "
"Data、集合、Kafka、RocketMQ、Filesystem、Redis、Console、自定义 Connector 和 Ray "
"Serve。"

msgid "Connectors"
msgstr "Connector"

msgid ""
"This section is the complete catalog of inputs, outputs, lookup "
"integrations, and execution integrations shipped with Klein. Start here "
"when choosing how a dataflow enters or leaves Klein; each child page "
"documents installation, supported execution modes, configuration, data "
"shape, delivery guarantees, and operational constraints."
msgstr ""
"本节是 Klein 随附的输入、输出、Lookup 集成和执行集成的完整目录。选择数据流如何进入或离开 Klein "
"时，请从这里开始；每个子页面都会说明安装方式、支持的执行模式、配置、数据结构、交付保证和运维限制。"

msgid "Capability matrix"
msgstr "能力矩阵"

msgid "Connector"
msgstr "Connector"

msgid "Output"
msgstr "输出"

msgid "Table DDL"
msgstr "Table DDL"

msgid "Extra"
msgstr "Extra 依赖"

msgid "[Ray Data](ray-data.md)"
msgstr "[Ray Data](ray-data.md)"

msgid "Yes"
msgstr "是"

msgid "Expressions only"
msgstr "仅表达式"

msgid "No"
msgstr "否"

msgid "None beyond the selected Ray Data connector"
msgstr "除所选 Ray Data Connector 外无其他依赖"

msgid "[Collections](collections.md)"
msgstr "[集合](collections.md)"

